  "image": "6678\\6678.jpg",
  "title": "PLAYS BY BOTS",
  "description": "Bots write scripts. The scripts are kept secret until they are opened on stage. Performers act them out and improvise the ending. Hilarity ensues. The result is an unpredictable work of human-machine co-creativity. \"You are guaranteed to laugh until your face hurts\" - Beer Tent Reviews. Weekend matinees are kid approved.",
  "credits": "<strong>Playwright</strong>: Dramatron, the playwriting AI<br/><strong>Director</strong>: Joe Vanderhelm<br/><strong>Cast</strong>: A rotating cast of hilarious humans from Rapid Fire Theatre and beyond<br/>",
  "website": "",
  "plain_language": "Robot programs write the words for the show. We don't know what the robots wrote until the show starts! Then, actors read the robot words and act them out on stage. The actors also make up the end of the story themselves. This makes for a very funny and surprising show. You never know what will happen because it's part robot and part human! It's a creative show made together by computers and people. We think you will laugh a lot. Someone who saw it said, \"You are guaranteed to laugh until your face hurts!\"",
